{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-03T21:17:25.561Z","tool_name":"run_shell_command","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777843045561_0","parameters":{"description":"Create the resources.md file.","command":"cat > resources.md << 'EOF'\n# Resources Catalog: Theory of Simulation\n\n## Summary\nThis catalog contains papers, datasets, and code gathered to investigate LLMs as multiverse simulators of human behavior.\n\n## Papers\n| Title | Authors | Year | File | Key Info |\n|-------|---------|------|------|----------|\n| Multiversal views on language models | Reynolds et al. | 2021 | papers/Multiversal_Views.pdf | Foundation: LLMs as multiverse generators. |\n| Role-Play with LLMs | Shanahan et al. | 2023 | papers/Role_play_with_LLMs.pdf | Theoretical bridge: Superposition of simulacra. |\n| Generative Agents | Park et al. | 2023 | papers/Generative_Agents_Smallville.pdf | Implementation: Social simulacra in Smallville. |\n| Homo Silicus | Horton | 2023 | papers/Homo_Silicus.pdf | Empirical: LLMs as economic agents. |\n| AgentSociety | Piao et al. | 2025 | code/AgentSociety | State-of-the-art: City-scale simulation. |\n\n## Datasets\n| Name | Source | Samples | Location | Notes |\n|------|--------|---------|----------|-------|\n| PersonaHub | proj-persona | 100 (sample) | datasets/PersonaHub/ | Diverse personas for seeding simulations. |\n| Reddit Confessions | SocialGrep | 100 (sample) | datasets/reddit_confessions/ | Raw human behavior/confessions data. |\n\n## Code Repositories\n| Name | URL | Purpose | Location |\n|------|-----|---------|----------|\n| generative_agents | joonspk-research/generative_agents | Core simulation engine | code/generative_agents/ |\n| homo_silicus | johnjosephhorton/homo_silicus | Economic experiment framework | code/homo_silicus/ |\n| AgentSociety | tsinghua-fib-lab/AgentSociety | Urban simulation framework | code/AgentSociety/ |\n\n## Recommendations for Experiment Design\n\n1. **Primary Methodology**: Use the **Multiverse Branching** approach described in Reynolds (2021). Start with a human behavior prompt (from Reddit Confessions) and roll out multiple parallel \"futures\".\n2. **Seeding**: Use `PersonaHub` to systematically vary the \"underlying factors\" (personas) of the simulated agents.\n3. **Verification**: Use the `Homo Silicus` methodology to verify if the simulated outcomes are consistent with human economic/psychological laws.\n4. **Scale**: If computational resources allow, adapt the `AgentSociety` framework to move from individual to collective behavior simulation.\n\n## Completion Marker\nThe resource finding phase is complete. All resources are organized and ready for the experiment runner.\nEOF\n"}}
